---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The :hidden: document attribute"
  description="The only document attribute that is not in the document attributes reference."
  robots="noindex,nofollow"
>
  <article class="mn-rendered mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="m-0 text-4xl font-extrabold text-[var(--mn-c-text-1)]">The <code>:hidden:</code> document attribute</h1>

    <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-[var(--mn-c-text-2)]">
      You found it. That makes it, by definition, no longer hidden — a
      contradiction the drafting committee has declined to resolve.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-[var(--mn-c-divider)] bg-[var(--mn-c-bg-elv)] p-6">
      <dl>
        <dt class="font-mono text-[15px] font-semibold text-[var(--mn-c-text-1)]"><code>:hidden:</code></dt>
        <dd class="mt-2 text-[var(--mn-c-text-2)]">
          Boolean, default <code>true</code>. Applies to all pages except this one.
          Causes the annotated element to be discussed only in meetings that
          did not happen, recorded in minutes that were never taken, and
          documented in references that do not cite it.
        </dd>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold text-[var(--mn-c-text-1)]">Usage</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--mn-c-text-2)]">
      <code>:hidden:</code> is the only document attribute that is not in the
      <a href="/author/ref/document-attributes/">document attributes reference</a>.
      Go ahead, check. We'll wait.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[var(--mn-c-text-2)]">
      It is applied to attributes that would prefer not to be discussed in
      public, pages that technically do not exist, and this paragraph.
      Related attributes, none of which you will find anywhere either:
      <code>:invisible:</code>, <code>:redacted:</code>, <code>:under-review:</code>,
      and <code>:do-not-document:</code>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold text-[var(--mn-c-text-1)]">How you got here</h2>
    <p class="text-[var(--mn-c-text-2)]">
      Nobody knows. This page is excluded from the sitemap and from search
      engines, which is exactly what a hidden attribute would want. If you
      arrived here from a link, that link does not exist either.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10">
      <a href="/" class="rounded-full bg-[var(--mn-c-brand-1)] px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white no-underline">
        Return to being visible
      </a>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
